        Official Singles Chart on 10/2/2017

        10 February 2017 - 16 February 2017

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        Ed Sheeran has set a new Official UK Singles Chart record this week. He has now held the Top 2 positions on the chart for five consecutive weeks, with "Shape Of You" at number 1 and "Castle On The Hill" at number 2. The previous record holder was Justin Bieber who held the Top 2 positions with "Sorry" and "Love Yourself" for four consecutive weeks in November/ December, 2015. I personally feel "Castle On The Hill" is a better song, but "Shape Of You" has a better video.

        "You Don't Know Me" by Jax Jones (feat RAYE) remains at number 3 this week. RAYE (whose real name is Rachel Keen) was short-listed for BBC Music Sound of... award for 2017 and finished in third place.

        "Big For Your Boot" by Stormzy debuts at number 8 this week. The song is the first single from his highly anticipated debut album "Gang Signs & Prayer".

        "No Favors" by Big Sean (feat Eminem) debuts at number 56.

        I haven't done a review for a couple of weeks but I'm doing one today.
        -Firstly, congratulations to Ed Sheeran for five weeks at both one and two with Shape Of You and Castle On The Hill- neither have shown any signs of dropping from those positions in the last couple of weeks, as I knew they wouldnt- Ed Sheeran's return was always going to be massive especially after the massive success of X.
        -However, he will receive competition next week. Firstly, Katy Perry's new song Chained To The Rhythm sounds pretty good at first listen, and she's entered into the top 15 on Spotify and top 5 on iTunes in the last day, so she will prove stiff competition I'm sure. Also, the release of Rag'N'Bone Man's new album has led to Human climbing on iTunes and Spotify- it is currently no2 on the former- ahead of castle on the hill! I cant say I'm a fan of the song- but it may still challenge Ed at least to 2 if not 1.
        -3 new songs entered into the top 10 today, something which has been somewhat of a rarity in recent times bar the legendary week Ed Sheeran, Jax Jones, Starley and JP Cooper all hit the top 10 in the same week! ;)
        -One of those was Big For Your Boots by Stormzy which enters the top 10 at first attempt. One thing ive found out in the last few days is that Stormzy's girlfriend features in the video- and she works at Trending Live on 4Music!
        -And I'm happy that I Don't wanna Live forever by Zayn and Taylor Swift finally entered the top 10 as the film nears release to cinemas. The motion picture soundtrack also came out yesterday so the song will only get bigger along with songs by Sia and Halsey.
        -Although No lie's fall in downloads led to it leaving the top 10, Dua Lipa entered the top 10 with Be The One this week, over a year after its original release. Well done to her for reaching the top 10 in the end though!
        -Dua also took a large climb with her Martin Garrix collaboration Scared To Be Lonely, from 23-14. Although this track is in the top 10 for neither iTunes nor Spotify at the moment, it could be her third top 10 in as many weeks next week.
        -Sage The Gemini also took a climb to reach his peak position of 17 with Now And Later. Although it looks unlikely to hit any higher a position, well done to him for reaching the top 20 with this song!
        -And the highest climb in the top 40 today was a jump of 10 places, tied between Text From Your Ex and Don't Leave- both songs have taken a while to gain momentum but it looks as if both will now.
        -I like both of the other new entries to the top 40, Train's Play That Song and James Arthur's Safe Inside. There isn't many songs of this kind reaching the charts these days, so I'm happy these made the top 40.
        -Just outside the top 40, Believer by Imagine Dragons entered at 42. I haven't heard it yet but I'm not a fan of rock so I'm not sure I will like it.         My thoughts & observations on the UK charts as always…
        - Ed Sheeran earns a fifth consecutive week at #1 on the singles chart with ‘Shape Of You’. I like the tropical inspiration to this song, which certainly makes it catchy & fun, but Ed has released better songs before & I can see this getting overplayed very soon. ‘Shape Of You’ leads both the sales & streaming charts for a fifth week & the airplay charts for a third.
        - With ‘Castle On The Hill’ remaining at #2, Ed Sheeran sets a new Official Charts record; he passes Justin Bieber for the most weeks that an artist has occupied the Top 2 spots. The former artist has now been at #1 with ‘Shape Of You’ & #2 with ‘Castle On The Hill’ for the past five weeks.
        - ‘Big For Your Boots’ by Stormzy is this week’s highest debut, entering the Official Charts at #8 & becoming his second Top 10 appearance after ‘Shut Up’ (also peaking at #8 on the 21/12/2015 chart after a campaign for Christmas #1). I’ll say that even though I hate his genre of rap (to the exception of Wiley), I really liked ‘Shut Up’. Although, I can’t stand ‘Big For Your Boots’ at all, with terrible production & aggressive lyrics. Unfortunately, a decent flow couldn’t stop me from hating this song. I hope it doesn’t stick around for long.
        - Our second of three new arrivals into the Top 10 is ‘I Don’t Wanna Live Forever’ by ZAYN & Taylor Swift, ascending 13-9 in its ninth week in the Top 100. It becomes ZAYN’s second Top 10 as a solo artist (he had 11 more with 1D) & Taylor’s ninth. I’m a huge fan of the latter artist here, so of course I’m happy to see this keep climbing. ZAYN delivers a good falsetto & Taylor’s upper range vocals work well here too. If I had to criticise it for anything, I would say that the song doesn’t really suit a movie like ‘Fifty Shades Darker’ that well, but overall, I’m very impressed!
        - A week after earning her first Top 10 hit last week with ‘No Lie’, Dua Lipa gets her second (first as lead artist) with ‘Be The One’, rising 11-10. I love the beat to this & Dua’s vocals here are so much better than some of her other previous hits. I actually knew about this song since late 2015 & even though it’s been over a year since the song’s original release, it was definitely worth the wait to see it reach the Top 10.
        - Below the Top 10, some of the biggest climbers are: ‘Scared To Be Lonely’ by Martin Garrix & Dua Lipa (23-14), ‘Text From Your Ex’ by Tinie Tempah ft Tinashe (34-24) & ‘Don’t Leave’ by Snakehips & MO (39-29). In order: the first is great, the second is meh & the third is decent.
        - Meanwhile, ‘Play That Song’ by Train leaps 47-25 this week. I much prefer: ‘Drops Of Jupiter’, ‘Hey, Soul Sister’ & ‘Drive By’ to this, but I have mixed thoughts on ‘Play That Song’; the trumpets in the hook make this a feel-good anthem, but Pat Monahan’s vocals aren’t great here.
        - ‘Safe Inside’ by James Arthur also enters the Top 40 by jumping 49-34 after its debut last week. It acts as the follow-up to the huge former #1 ‘Say You Won’t Let Go’ & I prefer this new song even more; great message & awesome vocals. I don’t think this will become big, but I’d like that to happen.
        - On the albums chart, ‘Little Fictions’ by Elbow debuts at #1, becoming their second #1 album. The rest of the Top 5 is: the ‘La La Land’ Motion Picture Cast Recording (1-2), ‘Glory Days’ by Little Mix (stationary at #3), ‘Classic House’ by Pete Tong & The Heritage Orchestra (2-4) & ‘x’ by Ed Sheeran (4-5).
        - Finally, I’m expecting a very high debut for ‘Chained To The Rhythm’ by Katy Perry; her first song since 'Rise' was released in July last year. The song features Skip Marley, who is Bob Marley’s grandson. I expect at least a Top 10 debut for this! At first listen, I can say that I think it’s very good, but I’m not calling it fantastic just yet.
        - Thanks for reading my review everyone. Enjoy your weekend! :)
